If you want to define a new web service, please follow the following steps:
# '''define credentials'''. # '''select method'''. # '''Define parameters'''. # Followed by '''choosing the result parts'''. # '''Define update policy'''. # Finally remember to '''Save the WWSD''' and '''enter the name''' of the web service.
{{Copyright of article |own work=True |copyright holder=Ontoprise GmbH |year=2010 |date retrieved=2010/04/12 }} [[UME discourse state::WebService| ]] [[UME link::Help:Defining a web service using GUI| ]] {{Content hash|value=}} {{Part of bundle|value=Smwusermanual}}

The special page '''''Special:DefineWebService''''', provides a graphical user interface which may be used to define the credentials of your web service. 
#'''Choose''' one of the protocols '''''SOAP''''' or '''''REST''''', depending on the web service you like to use.
#'''Enter''' the '''''URI of the web service''''', if you use a SOAP web service, the address (URI) has to direct to a WSDL file       (e. g. http://domain.de/soap_webservice.wsdl). You can optionally define '''''authentication credentials''''', currently only the basic HTTP authentication is supported.

