Follow the following steps to define parameters in a new web service: #First click on the ''' Add parameters'''-button thereby displaying the table that is used for defining parameters. #Then enter the '''path''' of the parameter. If you do not enter a path for a parameter this parameter will not be included into the WWSD. #Now enter an '''alias''' for the parameter, otherwise the parameter path will be used as alias.
*If a parameter is not required in a web service, you may mark this parameter as optional. If you mark a parameter as '''optional''' the users can call the web service without passing a value for this parameter. The users will otherwise get an error message. *If you define a '''default''' value for a parameter, this value will be used if a parameter is not optional and if no value for that parameter was passed to the web service call.
{{Copyright of article |own work=True |copyright holder=Ontoprise GmbH |year=2009 |date retrieved=2009/12/10 }} [[UME discourse state::WebService| ]] [[UME link::Help:Defining a web service using GUI| ]] {{Content hash|value=}} {{Part of bundle|value=Smwusermanual}}

There's generally no need to delete redirects. They do not occupy a significant amount of database space, and they do not show up in wiki search results. If a page name is vaguely meaningful there's no harm (and some benefit) in having it as a redirect to the most relevant existing page in your wiki. However... 

If you do need to delete a redirect, e.g. if the page name of the redirect is offensive, or you wish to discourage people from referring to concept by that name, then you simply go to the redirect page, and follow the same procedure for deleting a page. 

<br> 
