In SMW+ offers the possibility of importing and re-using the vocabulary which belongs to existing Semantic Web documents or standards by associating the vocabulary's elements with wiki terms.
An example of this functionality is the use of the [http://ontoworld.org/wiki/FOAF FOAF] vocabulary in the [http://ontoworld.org/wiki/Main_Page ontoworld.org] wiki. Although the associated terms work just like any other annotation in the wiki, the RDF that is exported will directly use the elements of the FOAF specification, thus allowing users to edit FOAF files through the wiki.
{{Copyright of article |own work=False |copyright holder=Semantic MediaWiki |year=2010 |date retrieved=2009/04/12 |answer=The special property imported from tells SMW+ that the wiki's property really refers to the property ''http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/knows'' from the FOAF vocabulary. |for_releases=all }} [[UME discourse state::DataImport| ]] [[UME link::Help:Import vocabulary| ]] {{Content hash|value=}} {{Part of bundle|value=Smwusermanual}}

