If you have a set of forms that all contain the same text or sections, you can avoid duplication by creating '''templates''' that are used within those forms.
#Simply place all the text that you want repeated within a template.
#Call that template within each form.
If that template contains form elements (like field definitions), the characters within the form elements simply need to be HTML-escaped - replace <nowiki>'{' with '&amp;#123;', '|' with '&amp;#124;' and '}' with '&amp;#125;'</nowiki>.

