Once you create a redirect, you may no longer get to that page name. The browser is always redirected! Looking at the top of the page you should see a link. Clicking on this link takes you back to the redirected page name, and&nbsp;'''view''' the redirect.
In doing this, you are able to do all the things that any wiki page allows you to. You may even go to the associated discussion page and talk about the redirect. You may also view the history of the page that existed before the redirect was created. One may also edit the page if the redirect was wrong and you may also revert to an older version so as to remove the redirect.
{{Copyright of article |own work=True |copyright holder=Ontoprise GmbH |year=2009 |date retrieved=2009/11/12 |answer=near the top of the page, a link is provided. Click this to get back to the redirected page name, and |for_releases=all }} [[UME discourse state::General| ]] [[UME link::Help:Handling redirects 1.5.3| ]] {{Content hash|value=}} {{Part of bundle|value=Smwusermanual}}

One template in each form should define each article that the form creates as being part of a certain category. You should create a page for each such cat-egory, and specify its default form so that every article may automatically be edited with the same form that created it. The easiest way to do that is using the '''CreateCategory''' special page. 
