{{Part of bundle|value=Smwusermanual}}

'''Semantic Forms''' is an extension to MediaWiki which allows users to add and edit data using forms. It is heavily tied in with the [http://semantic-mediawiki.org semantic-mediawiki.org] extension and is meant to be used for structured data that has semantic markup. Having '''Semantic MediaWiki''' installed is a precondition for the '''Semantic Forms''' extension; the code will not fully work without it.
Putting it simply, we can say that '''Semantic Forms''' allows you to have '''forms for adding and editing data''' on your wiki, '''without any programming'''. Forms can be created and edited not just by administrators, but also by the end users.
{{Copyright of article |own work=True |copyright holder=Ontoprise GmbH |year=2009 |date retrieved=2009/11/12 |answer=Semantic Forms is an extension to MediaWiki that allows users to add and edit data using forms |for_releases=all }} [[UME discourse state::EditWikisyntax| ]] [[UME discourse state::SemanticForms| ]] [[UME discourse state::SpecialPages| ]] [[UME link::Help:Semantic Forms Extension| ]] {{Content hash|value=}} {{Part of bundle|value=Smwusermanual}}

'''Data type''' is a defined kind of data. It is a set of possible values and basic operations on those values.

For instance: [http://semantic-mediawiki.org/wiki/Type:Page Page], [http://semantic-mediawiki.org/wiki/Type:String String], [http://semantic-mediawiki.org/wiki/Type:Text Text], [http://semantic-mediawiki.org/wiki/Type:Code Code], [http://semantic-mediawiki.org/wiki/Type:URL URL], [http://semantic-mediawiki.org/wiki/Type:Number Number], [http://semantic-mediawiki.org/wiki/Type:Date Date] ...

