'''Type:Numbe'''r allows a unit after the numeric value to distinguish values (e.g. "30 kg" versus "5 liter/100 km"), but does not know how to convert between them.
To support automatic conversion and multiple unit formats, you can define your own datatype with custom units. These automatically convert values to and from standard representations, so that you are free to use your preferred unit in each article yet still query and compare with property values in other articles.
{{Copyright of article |own work=True |copyright holder=Ontoprise GmbH |year=2009 |date retrieved=2009/11/12 |answer=Using different types, properties can be used to describe very different kinds of values |for_releases=all }} [[UME discourse state::EditWikisyntax| ]] [[UME discourse state::OntologyBrowser| ]] [[UME discourse state::Property| ]] [[UME discourse state::SemanticToolbar| ]] [[UME link::Help:Using custom units 1.5.3| ]] {{Content hash|value=}} {{Part of bundle|value=Smwusermanual}}

In order to understand what an edit conflict is, consider the following situation:
#Alice clicks '''Edit this page''' on a page. #Then Bob clicks '''Edit this page''' on this very same page and at this very time. #Alice finishes editing and clicks '''Save page'''. The page is saved with Alice's version. #Bob also finishes his edits and clicks '''Save page''' : Bob then gets an '''edit conflict page''' as a result of this coincidence.
{{Copyright of article |own work=False |copyright holder=MediaWiki |year=2009 |date retrieved=2009/12/11 |answer=This page discusses '''edit conflicts''', and how to deal with them |for_releases=all }} [[UME discourse state::EditWikisyntax| ]] [[UME link::Help:Solving edit conflicts 1.5.3| ]] {{Content hash|value=}} {{Part of bundle|value=Smwusermanual}}

Your extension containing a deploy descriptor (formal description of the deployable entity) is not registered with a DF tag in LocalSettings.php.<br>
'''Solution'''<br>
<tt>DF tags are constructs like:</tt><br>
 /*start-<ext-id>*/
 ...
 /*end-<ext-id>*/

<tt><ext-id> is replaced by the package ID of the extension.</tt><br>
<tt>Create a DF tag manually. Enclose all statements which belong to a particular extension by the tags above. </tt>

