The '''[http://blog.case.edu/bmb12/2006/09/geocoding_tools_for_python_and_caseclasses Geocoding Tools for Python]''' provide a simple toolkit for obtaining the geographic coordinates of places in the real world. For example, you can find out the location of some building you are at by providing the buildings name. The name is looked up in various sources, including semantic wikis, and the location is returned. Further [[Property:located in|located in]] statements are used to infer the location of sub-locations.

