The '''[http://ontoworld.org/wiki/Piggy_Bank Piggy Bank]''' is a browser extension for Firefox available at http://simile.mit.edu/piggy-bank/. Semantic MediaWiki refers to a page's RDF specification within its HTML header so that Piggy Bank can find it.
In effect, Piggy Bank will collect RDF of all visited articles during browsing. Of course, the further use of this RDF, as in all applications of Piggy Bank, is left to the user.
{{Copyright of article |own work=True |copyright holder=Ontoprise GmbH |year=2009 |date retrieved=2009/02/04 |answer=Geocoding Tools for Python, Tabulator, Longwell, FOAF Explorer, Piggy Bank, KAON2, OpenLink RDF Browser, and others |for_releases=all }} [[UME discourse state::General| ]] [[UME link::Help:Reuse| ]] {{Content hash|value=}} {{Part of bundle|value=Smwusermanual}}

The '''[http://ontoworld.org/wiki/OpenLink_RDF_Browser|OpenLink RDF Browser]''' is an independent Browser and Javascript based RDF Browser that is part of the [http://sourceforge.net/projects/oat OpenLink Ajax Toolkit] (OAT).
The deliverables includes a [http://demo.openlinksw.com/DAV/JS/demo/index.html live demonstration] that works with Semantic MediaWiki RDF Export pages.
