{{Content hash|value=}}
{{Part of bundle|value=Smwusermanual}}

When one opens an article in the '''Advanced Annotation Mode''' (or the edit mode), the semantic toolbar displays a green area that is labeled as '''Annotation hints'''. It contains all suggestions from the gardening bot about the current article.
Once you correct the problems, you should restart the gardening bots again so as to update the list of issues.
{{Copyright of article |own work=True |copyright holder=Ontoprise GmbH |year=2009 |date retrieved=2009/11/10 |answer=Gardening issues of an article are displayed in the list of annotation hints |for_releases=all }} [[UME discourse state::Annotate| ]] [[UME link::Help:Advanced Annotation Mode| ]] {{Content hash|value=}} {{Part of bundle|value=Smwusermanual}}

OntoSkin3 got its own footer, which can be customized by the WikiSysop. The modification information shown in the monobook footer, is directly displayed below the page content in OntoSkin3.
